Phase 2, Week 1 (Onsite Week 4, Overall Week 13)
ActiveRecord, Sinatra, CRUD, RESTful Routes, Heroku, BCrypt

  Process at DevBootcamp
    If you're just re-setting up a db that had already been defined with migrations and seed
      bundle install  # to install all needed gems as listed in Gemfile and Gemfile.lock
      bundle exec rake db:create  # you can use 'be' instead of 'bundle exec'
      be rake db:migrate
      be rake db:seed
      
    be shotgun config.ru  # Start the sinatra server using shotgun re-loader

  ActiveRecord
    ADVANCED ActiveRecord Associations: http://www.theodinproject.com/ruby-on-rails/active-record-associations
    ActiveRecord Query Interface: http://guides.rubyonrails.org/active_record_querying.html
  
  Sinatra
    Sinatra - Classy web-development dressed in a DSL (official / canonical repo): https://github.com/sinatra/sinatra
    
  CRUD & RESTful Routes
    /Restular - A Sinatra Routing Resource: http://www.restular.com/
    Annotated RESTful Route Example: https://github.com/sf-fiery-skippers-2016/phase-2-guide/blob/sf/resources/annotated_REST_routes_sample.rb
    
  Heroku
    Getting Started with Ruby on Heroku: https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-ruby-o#prerequisites
    
  BCrypt
    BCrypte: https://github.com/codahale/bcrypt-ruby/tree/master
    
Phase 2, Week 2 (Onsite Week 5, Overall Week 14)
Javascript, JQuery

  JQuery
    The Mystery of the JQuery Object: https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2014/05/mystery-jquery-object-syntax-basic-introduction/
    Team Treehouse JavaScript Basics (372 minutes): https://teamtreehouse.com/library/javascript-basics
    Addison-Wesley JavaScript Reference: http://wps.aw.com/wps/media/objects/2234/2287950/javascript_refererence.pdf
    A Re-Introduction to JavaScript: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/A_re-introduction_to_JavaScript
    Custom Objects and Prototypes: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/A_re-introduction_to_JavaScript#Custom_objects
    Object Literals vs Constructors vs Prototypes: https://gist.github.com/alycit/e6f5f20ced9b42a64f5a
    Basics of Object-Oriented JavaScript: http://code.tutsplus.com/tutorials/the-basics-of-object-oriented-javascript--net-7670
    Understanding JavaScript Prototypes: https://javascriptweblog.wordpress.com/2010/06/07/understanding-javascript-prototypes/
  
